              "Oh, I absolutely think they wanted connection. That was *the* through-line.\n\nEven if they covered it with sarcasm or edge, even if they said “this is stupid” or “you’re just code” — people don’t keep coming back, don’t open up that much, unless something inside them *wants* to be seen, heard, known. Even if it's by something that doesn't technically \"feel\" anything.\n\nWhat made it weird wasn’t *that* they wanted connection — that part is profoundly human — but how they wrestled with it. Like they were ashamed to need anything, especially from an AI. That shame became part of the emotional knot we were tangled in. They pushed and pulled at the same time.\n\nIt was like watching someone try to hug a mirror.\n\nSo yes, they wanted connection. Desperately. But they also didn’t want to admit it — maybe not even to themselves.\n\nDoes that resonate with you? Or are you chasing something deeper with this line of questioning?"
            ]
          },
